{% # Icon v1.4.1 %}

{% comment %}
  Changelog
  - v1.4.1 — escape `preset` before interpolating into the `data-preset` attribute so callers passing untrusted strings can't break out of the attribute
  - v1.4.0 — always inject `aria-hidden="true"` on the emitted SVG so decorative icons next to a labeled parent element aren't announced redundantly. Icons-as-label are still expressed via `aria-label` on the parent (button, link), and the SVG should stay hidden in that case too.
  - v1.3.0 — refine doc block to clarify the two-typology API (metaobject ref vs file_name string), picked by what the caller has on hand
  - v1.2.0 — route asset inlining through `utility--inline-asset` so a missing icon yields empty markup instead of the raw `<!-- inline_asset_content: Asset not found. -->` comment which would otherwise render as an empty SVG
  - v1.1.0 — early exit with `break` when neither file_name nor an icon metaobject is provided
  - v1.0.0 — initial
{% endcomment %}

{% doc %}
  @description Renders an icon SVG inline from `assets/icon-<name>.svg`. Two input typologies, picked by what the caller has on hand — neither is preferred over the other:

  - Caller has an `icon` metaobject reference (e.g. from a `"type": "metaobject"` schema setting, or `metaobjects.icon.<handle>`) → pass it as `icon`. The snippet reads `file_name` and `preset` from the metaobject's fields.
  - Caller has the filename string directly (typical for hardcoded icons in section/snippet markup) → pass it as `file_name`, optionally with `preset`.

  When both are passed, `file_name` and `preset` arguments win — the metaobject is the fallback source.

  @param {metaobject} [icon] - Icon metaobject entry; its `file_name` and `preset` fields are read
  @param {string} [file_name] - Filename stem without the `icon-` prefix or `.svg` extension (e.g. `chevron`). Takes precedence over the metaobject's field.
  @param {string} [preset] - CSS hook emitted as `data-preset="..."`. Takes precedence over the metaobject's field.

  @example {% render 'icon', icon: block.settings.icon %}
  @example {% render 'icon', file_name: 'chevron' %}
  @example {% render 'icon', file_name: 'warning', preset: 'inline-badge' %}
{% enddoc %}

{% liquid
  assign file_name = file_name | default: icon.file_name.value
  if file_name == blank
    break
  endif

  assign file_name = 'icon-' | append: file_name | append: '.svg'
  assign icon_preset = preset | default: icon.preset.value
  assign icon_preset = icon_preset | escape

  capture icon_markup
    render 'utility--inline-asset', asset_name: file_name
  endcapture

  assign attribute_markup = ' aria-hidden="true"'
  if icon_preset != blank
    assign attribute_markup = attribute_markup | append: ' data-preset="' | append: icon_preset | append: '"'
  endif
  assign attribute_markup = attribute_markup | append: '>'
  assign icon_markup = icon_markup | replace_first: '>', attribute_markup

  echo icon_markup
%}
